cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "lumi-assistant: an opencode configuration for a general CERN assistant"
abstract: >
  A configuration bundle for the opencode / lumi agent CLI, providing
  intent-organised skills, sub-agent personas, remote MCP wiring
  (atlasopenmagic, cernopendata, cerndocs) and CVMFS-deployable
  packaging for a general CERN assistant covering service operations
  (Rucio, FTS, REANA, HTCondor), computing, and physics analysis —
  from the public ATLAS / CERN Open Data releases to internal
  analysis frameworks — on lxplus, SWAN, Binder, Colab, and local
  Jupyter installs.
type: software
authors:
